in the Lord of the Rings series, captures the ravaging effects of sin perfectly with the devolution of the hobbit Simegal into that vile and decrepit creature of shadow and filth Gollum, whose body and psyche are both slowly mutated and destroyed over the centuries by the corrupting influence of the One Ring.

